{"altmetric_id":3804206,"counts":{"readers":{"mendeley":3,"citeulike":0,"connotea":0},"total":{"posts_count":1},"twitter":{"unique_users_count":1,"unique_users":["MBHolistic"],"posts_count":1}},"selected_quotes":["#Alternative Bidens pilosa Formulation Improves Blood Homeostasis and \u03b2-Cell Function in Men... #health #research"],"citation":{"abstract":"B. pilosa has long been purported to have antidiabetes activity, but despite the advancement in phytochemistry and animal models of diabetes, no human clinical trials have been conducted to date. Here, we evaluated the effect of a B. pilosa formulation on fasting blood glucose (FBG), fasting serum insulin, and glycosylated hemoglobin A1c (HbA1c) in diabetic subjects. The B. pilosa formulation reduced the level of FBG and HbA1c in diabetics but increased fasting serum insulin in healthy subjects. Moreover, combination of B. pilosa formulation with antidiabetic drugs had better glycemic control in diabetics. The homeostatic model assessment (HOMA) data suggested that the antidiabetic activity of this formulation was via improvement of \u03b2-cell function. We also tested the safety of the B. pilosa formulation in healthy subjects and observed no obvious side effects. We conclude that B. pilosa has potential as an antidiabetes treatment.","altmetric_jid":"4f6fa5243cf058f610003c64","authors":["Lai, Bun-Yueh"],"doi":"10.1155\/2015\/832314","first_seen_on":"2015-03-18T17:01:37+00:00","funders":["niehs"],"issns":["1741-427X"],"journal":"Evidence-based Complementary & Alternative Medicine (eCAM)","last_mentioned_on":1426698085,"links":["http:\/\/www.hindawi.com\/journals\/ecam\/2015\/832314\/"],"pdf_url":"http:\/\/downloads.hindawi.com\/journals\/ecam\/2015\/832314.pdf","pmid":"25866541","pubdate":"2015-04-14T22:01:32+00:00","publisher":"Hindawi Publishing Corporation","publisher_subjects":[{"name":"Complementary And Alternative Medicine","scheme":"era"}],"scopus_subjects":["Medicine","Health Sciences"],"title":"<i>Bidens